<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="94" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="23" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,691,717]" pageId="23" pageNumber="94">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[850,886,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="94">tri-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[939,1021,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="94">lobatus</emphasis>
, referring to the three papillary lobes of the juxta on the posterior margin.
</paragraph>
